commentTextItems.html: bouncer, pulled to midwicket for four and that's the win to Zimbabwe. The series is drawn 1-1.

commentPostTextItems.html: An impressive win for Zimbabwe. Scotland's batters, apart from Coetzer and MacLeod failed to put on anything serious, and threw away their wickets. Zimbabwe had a little wobble when they were 44-3, but after lunch, they built their innings back and
deserved to fully win. It was a superb performance from batting, to bowling to their fielding.

milestones.description: Graeme Cremer has taken the most five-wicket hauls (3) in ODIs for ZIM, going past Brian Vitori's record
This is the lowest match aggregate (340) involving teams Zimbabwe & Scotland in ODIs
Kyle Coetzer has scored 4 hundreds in ODIs, the most for SCOT breaking Calum MacLeod's record
Berrington has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (55) for SCOT, going past Majid Haq

stories.seoTitle: Kyle Coetzer renews Scotland plea for more opportunities
stories.summary: Kyle Coetzer has said Scotland, after putting in stellar performances against Full Member nations, deserve more chances than they're currently getting

stories.seoTitle: Zimbabwe level series courtesy Graeme Cremer's five-wicket haul
stories.summary: Sikandar Raza's half century helped Zimbabwe chase down Scotland's target of 170 with 13 overs to spare
stories.byline: The Report by Peter Della Penna in Edinburgh

image.caption: Graeme Cremer celebrates after winning an lbw appeal to claim Richie Berrington's wicket

stories.title: Improved Scotland chase history again
stories.subTitle: Scotland v Zimbabwe, 2nd ODI, Edinburgh
stories.summary: Having picked up their first ODI win over a Full Member nation, Scotland will now target a maiden ODI series win over a Full Member, while Zimbabwe fight to avoid a series sweep
stories.byline: The Preview by Peter Della Penna in Edinburgh

image.caption: Con de Lange celebrates his fifth wicket after Malcolm Waller is caught on the boundary
image.longCaption: Con de Lange celebrates his fifth wicket after Malcolm Waller is caught on the boundary, Scotland v Zimbabwe, 1st ODI, Edinburgh, June 15, 2017

videos.title: 'Maybe we needed to lose first game' - Cremer
videos.subTitle: SCOTLAND V ZIMBABWE, 2ND ODI
videos.seoTitle: 'Maybe we needed to lose first game' - Graeme Cremer
videos.summary: Zimbabwe captain Graeme Cremer talks about the importance of their defeat to Scotland in the first ODI and how it helped the team stage a comeback and level the series in the second game

videos.title: Zimbabwe bowled us out with their spin - Coetzer
videos.subTitle: SCOTLAND V ZIMBABWE, 2ND ODI
videos.seoTitle: Zimbabwe bowled us out with their spin - Kyle Coetzer
videos.summary: Scotland captain Kyle Coetzer reflects on his side's inability to deal with Zimbabwe's spin bowling in their ODI loss at Raeburn Place

stories.title: Coetzer renews Scotland plea for more opportunities
stories.subTitle: Scotland news
stories.seoTitle: Kyle Coetzer renews Scotland plea for more opportunities
stories.summary: Kyle Coetzer has said Scotland, after putting in stellar performances against Full Member nations, deserve more chances than they're currently getting
